      • validateName

        public static boolean validateName(java.lang.String string)
        Checks that the given name matches the requirements for names.

        Used to check airline name, alias, call sign and country; airport name, city and country; and flight point id.

        Currently always returns true. Included for completeness and for maintainability against the possibility of constraints being placed on names.

        Parameters:
        string - the name to check
        Returns:
        true

      • validateDaylightSavingTime

        public static boolean validateDaylightSavingTime(java.lang.String string)
        Checks that the string represents a daylight savings time indicator. That is, that the string is one of "E" (Europe), "A" (US/Canada), "S" (South America), "O" (Australia), "Z" (New Zealand), "N" (None) or "U" (Unknown)
        Parameters:
        string - the string to check
        Returns:
        true if the string is a valid daylight savings time flag, else false

      • validateTimezoneDB

        public static boolean validateTimezoneDB(java.lang.String string)
        Checks that the string represents a valid timezone database, in olson format.

        Checks that the string contains only alphanumeric characters, forward slash, hyphen and underscores.

        Parameters:
        string - the string to check
        Returns:
        true if the string is valid, else false
        See Also:
        Wikipedia: tz database

      • validateFlightPointType

        public static boolean validateFlightPointType(java.lang.String string)
        Checks that the given string is a valid flight point type. That is, it is one of

        "UKN" - Unknown

        "APT" - Airport

        "NDB" - Non-directional beacon (NDB)

        "VOR" - VHF omni-directional range (VOR)

        "FIX" - Navigational fix

        "DME" - Distance measuring equipment

        "LATLON" - Latitude/Longitude point

        Parameters:
        string - the string to check
        Returns:
        true if the string is valid, else false
        See Also:
        Flight Plan Database: API specs
